<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
    Certificate pinning - MONITOR-ONLY mode (Iteration 1 - NewDot, release builds).

    Pin validation runs in CertificatePinning.kt (OkHttp), WebViewCertificateMonitor.kt (WebView),
    and ios/CertificatePinning.swift (TrustKit). Mismatches are reported to Sentry but connections
    are NOT blocked.

    Android <pin-set> always blocks on mismatch and cannot run in monitor-only mode, so this file
    intentionally contains NO pin-sets during the monitor rollout. Monitor-mode coverage per channel:

        Channel                Coverage during monitor mode
        ──────────────────     ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
        OkHttp (fetch, RN)     ✓  CertificatePinning.kt monitor interceptor
        Fresco (RN Image)      ✓  Uses OkHttp via OkHttpClientProvider
        WebView                ✓  WebViewCertificateMonitor.kt (SPKI check after page load)
        HttpURLConnection      ✓  CertificatePinning.kt wrapping HostnameVerifier
        Glide (OldDot only)    ✗  Not used in NewDot; covered by HybridApp iteration

    When flipping to enforce mode:
      1. Set enforcePinning=true in config/certificatePinning/pins.json, CertificatePinning.kt, and
         CertificatePinning.swift.
      2. Replace this file's contents with network_security_config_enforce.xml.

    Debug builds use res/xml/network_security_config_debug.xml (no pinning) so local dev servers and
    proxy tooling (Charles/Proxyman) keep working.
-->
<network-security-config />
